    "summary": "This base-catalyzed nucleophilic ring-opening reaction was conducted in a cyclic continuous-flow reactor with 1.2 mm internal diameter tubing at 60°C using EtOAc as solvent. The flow process achieved 96% yield with a 60-minute residence time at 0.5 mL/min flow rate, compared to 93% yield requiring 20 hours in batch mode. The cyclic continuous-flow setup enabled a dramatic 20-fold reduction in reaction time (from 20 hours to 1 hour) while improving yield by 3 percentage points. The flow advantage likely stems from enhanced mass transfer and more consistent reaction conditions in the continuous system compared to the prolonged batch heating required for completion.",
